article.headline: Golden Knights no match for Bulldogs
article.linkText: Golden Knights no match for Bulldogs
article.story:
ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Doceide Warren came off the bench to score 15 points and grab seven rebounds in 14th-ranked Mississippi State's 81-30 rout of Central Florida on Friday.

Warren was one of four Bulldogs who scored in double figures as Mississippi State (8-1) won its sixth straight game and fifth straight on the road. The blowout victory included a 28-0 run in the second half.

UCF (4-5) shot 23.5 percent from the field in the game, scored
only 13 points in the second half and did not have a double-figure
scorer.

Warren hit three straight 3-pointers and Tan White added a
fourth as the Bulldogs raced out to an 18-8 lead. In all,
Mississippi State went 12-of-21 on 3-point attempts, including
6-of-9 in the first half.

After UCF's Shayla Smith opened the second half with a short jumper to cut the deficit to 39-19, the Golden Knights then went more than 12 minutes without scoring a point.

LaToya Thomas scored 13 points while White and Seneca Anderson
each had 12 points for Mississippi State.
